<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Submission to the Energy &amp; Climate Change Committee’s inquiry</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Supplementary written evidence submitted by Alex Henney (IPC0056)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The whole aim of practical politics is to keep the populace alarmed (and hence clamorous to be led to safety) by </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">menacing it with an endless series of hobgoblins, all of them</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> imaginary.”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">H.L. Mencken</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">INTRODUCTION</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> AND SUMMARY</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">The role of the IPCC</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In considering the matter at hand it is crucial </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">to appreciate the role of the IPCC, which is set out in “Principles </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">governing IPCC work”</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> “[The IPCC] shall concentrate its activities on the tasks allotted to it by the relevant WMO Executive Council and UNEP Governing Council resolutions and decisions as well as on actions in support of the UN Framework Convention on Cl</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">imate Change process</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The role of the IPCC is to assess on a comprehensive, objective, open and transparent basis the scientific, technical and socio-economic information relevant to understanding the scientific basis of risk of human-induced climate change</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, its potential impacts and options for adaptation and mitigation. IPCC reports should be neutral with respect to policy…”. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">These statements make it clear that the IPCC is not an academic scientific </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">organization </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">that it has clear governmental – hence</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> political – input.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">  Furthermore its aim is not to investigate the reasons for changes in the climate, but to seek out “human induced climate change” – which presupposes there is such climate change.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">At the end of September the IPCC published versions of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the Working Group 1 (WG1) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">report “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The Physical Science Basis</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">” and the related “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Summary </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">for </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Policy Makers</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> (SPM)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; the former was prepared by scientists, the latter by a mix of scientists and representatives of governments</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  The comments here are more often </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">made about the SPM, which is the more widely read document.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">The character of the submissions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There are </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> submissions</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of which two did not appear relevant to the matter at hand</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and two were from organisations that had an obvious commercial interest in promoting anthropogenic climate change (ACC)</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Of the remaining </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">41</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> submissions:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">11 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">from </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the “British warmist establishment” are supportive </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of the IPCC’s work.  One of these </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">submissions was by an independent scientific writer (Cowie).  Led </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">by DECC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">eight</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">were </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">organizations dominated by British </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">state scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">” (i.e. those either directly employed by the government or reliant upon it for grants)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. To those </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">added the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">submissions by the “Granthams” at the London School of Economics</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and Imperial College </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">One (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Gadian</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">), while believing that there are significant climate changes afoot, had a different and critical take on some issues</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">10 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">” scientists who are</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> critical of some or many aspects of the IPCC’s conclusions</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">19 are by public policy analysts</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; all but one are very cri</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">tical of the IPCC’s work</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">A</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ssessment of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">A</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ssessment</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The British warmist establishment accepted with few caveats the views expressed by </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the IPCC, singing from the same hymn sheet:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The conclusions of the AR5 Physical Science Basis Report are robust and there is little to question</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Much, if not most, of the science is settled – there are, however, a few areas of uncertainty</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 reflects </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the views of most scientists</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 confirms the need for urgent global action to address climate change </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC is an effective mechanism for assessing scientific knowledge and it has not been politicized</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 supports the government’s effort to cut CO2 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">emissions </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">All </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">submissions avoided discussion of, or attempted to finesse the unreliability of models</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and consequently none addressed the question of the magnitude of natural variability; all danced around the issue of whether AR5 has sufficiently </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">explained the hiatus in the global surface temperature; none addressed the empirical mea</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">surement of climate sensitivity.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In adopting their approach that “all was for the best of all possible worlds”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> re the IPCC’s work</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, the warmists ignored 1) the IPCC’s </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">past promotion of pseudo science such as the “hockey stick” and “Himalayagate”; 2) its past baseless claims of increased hurricanes and the spread of malaria due to ACC; 3) the exposure in Climategate of the unethical practices of a coterie of climate scie</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ntists involved with the IPCC; 4) its association with the inconvenient inaccuracies promoted by Senator Al Gore; and 5) the various shortcomings of both science and process discussed </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in this submission.  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">From the sceptic’s perspective they live in a Briti</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">sh bubble of consensus about settled science that is not disturbed by the reality outside the bubble!</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> scientists included some leading North American </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">climate </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">scientists and a physicist of international stature</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, who provides </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the advantage of an</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> independent p</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">er</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">spective from the debates that vex climate scientists.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The main scientific criticisms of AR5 are:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There is no substantive evidence to support the IPCC’s claimed linkage between the warming of the climate and increasing CO2</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> – the conclusions of the IPCC are not robust; there is scope to question many aspects of the science</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It convey</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> “an alarmist evaluation of the influence on the climate of anthropogenic CO2 emissions that does not properly reflect scientific knowledge”, with distortions for political purposes</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The models </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">do not reflect reality</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; can be fudged with high climate sensit</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ivity; and “are not getting any better”.  They are of little or no value in explaining the past, let alone forecasting the future</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The handling of uncertainties (e.g. claiming something is 95% certain) is shocking and deeply unscientific”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There was a fai</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lure to assess climate sensitivity from observational estimates which are suggesting much lower figures than used in the IPCC models</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">re was a failure to examine natural variability; the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">role of clouds and water vapour</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> are not properly understood; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ontribution of methane has not been properly analysed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the possible effect of the sun was effectively dismissed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  The science is definitely not settled</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Several propose that the IPCC is past its sell by date, and some argue there is a need for a genuinely </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">independent assessment of the realities of climate science</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“AR</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">5 conclusions fatally weaken the economic case for policy action. Both the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">level of, and confidence in, temperature </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">projections are sharply reduced”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There are factual errors in the science</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The public policy analysts (and some of the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> scientists) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">argue </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">that the IPCC process is not all that it is cracked up to be, notably:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It is not exclusively the work of independent scientists. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> The chairman; the head of WG1; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and some of the lead </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">authors have strong green activist credentials</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  “The IPCC authors were selected because they were known to agree with the consensus”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The growing implications of the complexity of the climate change problem and its potential solutions are becoming increa</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">singly apparent, highlighting the inadequacies of the ‘consensus to power’ approach for decision making on the complex issues associated with climate change” - </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">there are many unknowns in climate science</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Apart from Britain where climate science is </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">dominated by politically correct state scientists, there is no sound basis for claims of an international consensus</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It uses evasive and obfuscatory wording to cover over issues which are embarrassing</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> to its main story</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The proposal to rely on renewables </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> reduce CO2 emissions </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is impracticable given 1) their high costs and 2) their profligate use of land</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There is general agreement among the commentators that the SPM is a p</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">olitically contrived document. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC has failed to ensure any compliance with its </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">fundamental principle of requiring a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“comprehensive, objective, open and transparent” </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">process</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The British attempts at decarbonisation are both ineffectual, expensive, illusory tokenism that will not nothing to save the planet</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">TH</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">E BRITISH WARMIST </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ESTABLISHMENT</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">DECC</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">DECC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> stated “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">that the conclusions of the AR5 Physical Science Basis report are robust.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> The report was produced by over 850 independent expert scientists, all leaders in their fields</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> (209 Lead Authors, 50 Review Editors and Over 600 Contributing Authors</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">).</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> The report took over 2 years to produce and underwent multiple rounds of expert review.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> It was also reviewed by the 194 governments which form the IPCC.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> They have all accepted th</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e findings.”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">DECC c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">laimed “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC is a highly effective</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">mechanism for assessing scientific knowledge. It is</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">independent, transparent and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">attracts top scientists who give of their own time to participate</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. It has well laid out procedures and is open to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> both expert and Government Review. We see no evidence that it has deliberately sought to justify political commitment or indeed to propose a policy response.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">DECC has backed down from a previous claim by Secretary of State </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Davey </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">that “the science is set</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">tled” to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> the more modest claim that</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> “much of the climate science may reasonably be considered, in an everyday sense, to be settled…For example…rising concentrations of greenhouse gases (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">which no one disputes</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">),</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">a warming wo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">rld</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">but it has not warmed for 16</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> or so</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> years</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">), and related effects such as ice loss (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">but ice in the Antarctic has increased</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">) and the sea level has risen (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">which has continued at the same rate as for several </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">centuries</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Then it admits “However, the complexities of clouds and various feedb</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ack</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> mechanisms add uncertainties”.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">t is</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, however,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> not clear whether the reference</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> to feedback mechanisms</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is an allusion to the uncertainty over the magnitude of climate sensitivity to the level of CO2</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">DECC </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">avoided the question of the validation of</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> the climate models</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, and of the temperature pause</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It does not mention </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the possible effect of the sun on </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">climate.  Instead of these</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> fundamental </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">issues the submission refers to ignorance of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">what are in effect </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">secondary issues.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">     </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">State scientists</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he submission</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> by organizations dominated by state scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> who </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">generally </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">have to be politically correct either </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">get jobs (e.g. in the Met Office) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">or to get</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> grant</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> funding</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and m</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">any </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">m </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">have been heavily involved in the IPCC process</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  They </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">naturally </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">support the AR5 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">story</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lines</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">often </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in certain, if not dogmatic, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">terms</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span 