Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he warming for the last 16</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">years! Finally the SPM has totally ignored the reality of earth’s climate, which is that</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The earth’s climate now appears to be entering into a colder epoch!” With the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">approaching of the solar grand minima in the next decade or a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">bout, there is now a distinct</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">possibility that the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">earth’s climate could see an onset of an </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Ice Age type climate </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">next two to three decades!</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Nicholas Lewis </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is an independent self-funded </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">American </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">climate researcher whose specialism is climate sensitivity.  He points out that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There are two principal issues with the IPCC’s handling of the climate sensitivity area</span><a name="_ftnref15"></a><a href="#_ftn15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Firstly the inclusion of sensitivity estimates from flawed observational studies tha</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">t used</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">unsuitable data, were poorly designed and/or employed inappropriate statistical</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">methodology</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">[Lewis is very critical of the poor statistical methodology of climate scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">].</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">at obscured what should have been a key message from AR5 – that the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">be</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">st observational evidence now points to the climate system being substantially less</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sensitive to greenhouse gases than previously thought. Secondly, the elevation of computer</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">models over observational evidence. Virtually all the projections of future clima</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">te change</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in AR5 are based on simulations by</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> General Climate Models</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> despite these being out of line with the best</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">observational evidence.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He argues that “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">A particularly robust way of empirically estimating climate sensitivity is the so-called</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">‘energy-budget’ method, which is based on a fundamental physical law – the conservation</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of energy. Energy-budget best estimates of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ECS fall</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in a range between 1.5°C and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">2.0°C (1.25–1.4°C </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">for TCR</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">), depending on the exact periods chosen for analysis. Using</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he longest available periods that were free of major volcanism gives a ECS best estimate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of approximately 1.7°C (1.3°C for TCR)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">For the shorter-term TCR measure, the discrepancy between the average of the best</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">observational estimates is, at 1.4°C, also sub</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">stantially lower than the average of the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">GCM value of 1.8°C, but close to the energy budget estimate based on the best AR5 data</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of 1.3°C.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Richard Lindzen</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, Emeritus Professor, Department of Earth, Atmospheric and Planetary Sciences of MIT</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> is a leading US climate scientist.  He comments that “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The claim that 51% of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the small warming over the past 60 years</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is due to man’s activities is completely consistent with there being no problem worth bothering</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">about. The concern arises because of the c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">laim that models with high sensitivity can still be</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">fudged…to replicate the observed warming…As concerns the more serious questions such as what the sensitivity of the climate is or</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">what the relationship is between global warming and various purported disa</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sters, even the IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">generally admits to ignorance…As the attached paper notes, virtually all observational tests point to sensitivity less than that of any models, and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">there is no evidence of any relationship between extreme weather and global warm</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ing.”  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">His </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">submission includes </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">his</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> paper “Falsification of climate models used in experimentation and scenario construction” which explains how the models are constructed and their limitations.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In a blog he observed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“I think that the latest IPCC report has truly</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> sunk to level of hilarious incoherence. They are proclaiming increased confidence in their models as the discrepancies between their models and observations increase.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Non Intergovernmental International Panel on Climate Change (NIPCC) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">submission was prepared by well known climate scientists Craig Idso, Bob Carter, and Fred Singer based on the reports which NIPCC has published.  The submission states:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The conclusions of AR5 are not robust</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC has not addressed criticisms of previo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">us reports</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The report’s conclusions should be vigorously criticized</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The implicit consensus claimed by AR5 does not reflect reality</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 still defends models</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 has not explained the reasons for the hiatus</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 weakens the already weak case for action</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Roger</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Pielke</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> is Emeritus Professor of Atmospheric Science at Colorado State University; he was State Climatologist for Colorado and served as President of the American Association of State Climatologists.  He stated (with backing evidence provided) that “the IP</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">CC AR5 Physical Science Assessment:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">nadequately considered the spectrum of</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">human and natural climate forcings and feedbacks. Changes in climate are not</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">dominated by the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">human input of greenhouse gases</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ailed to report the lack of skill of multidecadal</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">climate model predictions (projections) to predict changes in regional climate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">statistics when run in hindcast simulations. Such a test is a requirement in the scientific</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">method if one is to have any confidence in its skill to predict future changes in reg</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ional</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> climate”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">PUBLIC POLICY CRITICS</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Barry Brill</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, formerly a Minister of Science and Energy in the New Zealand Government, comments:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“A</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">R5 temperature projections fail to reflect the current internal IPCC disagreement</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">regarding climate sensitivity </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and i</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ts contribution to ‘the hiatus’…:-</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“AR5 is unable to identify/quantify the reasons for, or the duration of the hiatus…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC models did not forecast ‘the hiatus’, and were not even close</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“In August 2013, IPPC lead author Dr Hans von Storch, told </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Speigel Online:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“So far, no one has been able to provide a compelling answer to why climate change seems to be taking a break.... There are two conceivable explanations -- and neither is very pleasant for us. The first possibility is that less global war</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ming is occurring than expected because greenhouse gases, especially CO2, have less of an effect than we have assumed. ... The other possibility is that, in our simulations, we have underestimated how much the climate fluctuates owing to natural causes.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“During 2011-13, at least 16 peer-reviewed journal papers have used recent data and modern diagnostics to show that this historical ‘best estimate’ [of climate sensitivity] had been grossly over-stated. All find that the ‘most likely’ ECS figure is around </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">1.5-2°C – and likely to be within a range of 1-3.5°C (not 1.5-4.5°C as applied in AR5)”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">For the first time, the IPCC finds itself unable to reach consensus on a ‘most likely’ sensitivity (ECS) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">[E</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">quilibrium clim</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ate sensitivity, see footnote 14</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">] </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">figure. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There are two distinct (and mutually exclusive) schools of thought at about 1.7°C and 3°C respectively. If the former group is correct (so the TCR is &lt;1.5°)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> [Transient C</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">limate Response, see footnote 14</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">]</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, virtually all warming projections become benign and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">policy action unjustified.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">If a TCR of 1.5°C is adopted, RCP4.5 [RCP=representative concentration pathways, a term introduced by the IPCC] provides a warming range of 1.1 to 1.6°C. Deducting t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he 0.72°C that occurred pre-199</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">4, this leaves 0.38-0.88°C as </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">likely </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">temperature increase during the 21st century (midpoint less than the 20th century). If the most likely estimate of ECS proves to be less than 2°C, AR5 does not project worrisome future warming, or sea level rise, except in the extreme case of RC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">P8.5.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Despite obscure language, the SPM accepts that the 1998-2012 warming of</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">0.05±0.15°C was not significant, and that a cooling trend (also insignificant) has obtained</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">throughout the 21st Century. Both trends discredit the CMIP3 and CMIP5</span><a name="_ftnref16"></a><a href="#_ftn16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> climate models,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">which have consistently projected warming of 2-3°</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">C/decade throughout this period”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">At Stockholm, no AR5 consensus could be reached on the first and most obvious explanation – exaggerated sensitivity.  Brill notes “Leaked draft reports indi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">cate much disputation within the IPCC about acceptance of the new and lower sensitivity figures</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Consequently, the projections appearing in Table SPM.2 do not reflect the TCR parameter now recommended in the WG1 report. In a word, they are incorrect. The AR</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">5 is </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">not internally consistent</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“AR</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">5 conclusions fatally weaken the economic case for policy action. Both the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">level of, and confidence in, temperature </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">projections are sharply reduced”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Marcel Crok </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a Dutch freelance science writer who published a critica</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">l book in 2010 that focused on A</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">3 and AR4.  He notes that AR5 failed to give an estimate for climate sensitivity that implied warming will be less than previously anticipated.  He draws attention to the IPCC’s failure to address the significance of “long </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">term persistence”.  When taken into account, the statistical significance of the 0.8</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">C warming since 1860 “is seriously overestimated”.  He also notes how AR5 uses presentational devices to finesse the reliability of models and to avoid accepting that the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Transient Climate Response in the models is “considerably higher than based on best observational evidence.”  He concludes “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The case for mitigation is less urgent and this means that as a society we could first focus on new</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">technologies that make decarboni</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sation possible with lower costs than the now available options like</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">wind, solar, biomass etc.”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Ruth Dixon </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is in t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he Department of Politics and International Relations</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> at Oxford University</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">She commented </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">that “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">If the IPCC reports are to be seen as truly </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">authoritative, a far more challenging review process</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">should be instituted. This could take the form of a ‘Red Team’ in which experts from other</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">scientific disciplines would be commissioned to undertake a critical review of the IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">reports, in whole or in </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">part.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Her submission is the least critical of the IPCC.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Jonathan Drake </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">professional physicist who has spent much free time engaged in independent climate research</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  He comments that “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Any and every piece of data that can be</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">forced to support the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Anthropogenic Global Warming (aka Climate Change) belief has been</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">seized upon without due diligence or regard</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> to normal scientific practices…t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">here was a great deal of secrec</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">y involved at all stages of AR5.”  He concludes “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC mechanism for assessing s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">cientific knowledge has numerous flaws, not least the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">fact that it has been established that there are many authors with biases, whether they are</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">vested interests (grants/funding), political or ideological, or simply just assumed prestige.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Robin Guenier </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a barrister with a varied career in business and as CEO of the Central Computing and Telecommunications Agency reporting to the Cabinet Office.  He examines the question </span><span style="color:#262626; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">To what extent does AR5 reflect the range of views among climate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">scientists?”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He examined the three studies (Doran, Anderegg and Cook) most commonly cited as claiming that most climate experts (usually 97%) agree humans are causing warming. He concluded that the “unsatisfactory nature of these studies means they can make only a limi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ted contribution to this submission”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He looked at other evidence, “from a 2008 study conducted by Dennis Bray and Hans von Storch, from a more recent American Meteorological Society study </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">[</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">that found only </span><span style="color:#262626; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">52% agree that most of the warming since 1850 is a</span><span style="color:#262626; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">nthropogenic] </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">from within the SPM itself and from, in particular, China.  They suggest that the AR5 findings only marginally reflect climate scientists’ views”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He concluded: “(a) there is insufficient evidence to support a satisfactory answer to the Commi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ttee’s question; (b) the only way to establish a satisfactory answer would be to carry out a full, properly conducted worldwide opinion survey (considered likely to be impracticable); and (c) such evidence as does exist indicates that the answer may well b</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e that AR5 reflects climate scientists’ views to only a very limited extent.”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Alex Henney</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> specializes in electric markets and regulation.  He has taken an interest in climate science because of the manner in which the government’s belief in ACC </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is destroying </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the electricity market and is adding to costs.  He </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">pointed to errors in some of the science that the IPCC had promoted</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in the past</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, and cites Professor Don Easterbrook as identifying factual errors in AR5.  Easterbrook commented o</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">f the IPCC c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">laim that “Warming of the climate system is unequivocal, and since the 1950s, many of the observed changes are unprecedented over decades to millenia…there just isn’t any nice way to say this—it’s is an outright lie.” </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He points to other errors and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">conclude</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s “These are only a few examples of the highly biased, misrepresentations of material in the 2013 IPCC report.  As seen by the examples above, it isn’t science at all – it’s dogmatic, political, propaganda.”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Hen</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ey drew attention t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">o the lack of reliabilit</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">y of climate models. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He noted that a scientist at the Hadley Centre forecast in 2000 that “British children could have only virtual experience of snow”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and in 2007 climate scientists at the Met Office used their new climate model to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">(incorrectly) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">forecast</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> 0.3</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">C warming over the decade 2004-2014.  He applied Richard Feynman’s concept of “cargo cult science” to climate models</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, and argues</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">If climate science were a “normal” science </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">failure of the models to predict the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">temperature pause would lead many </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">scientists to conclude that the assumptions underlying</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the models were wrong and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">they </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">would </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">go back to the drawing b</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">oard</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. But climate science is</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">politicised with extensive commercial, reputational and grant funding vested interests</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">hanging on it. So the IP</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">CC tries to massage the failure of the climate models and absurdly</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">to claim an increased confidence in the models as the discrepancy between models and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">observations increase.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He drew attention to papers that attributed much of climate change to changes i</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">n solar activity</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and to a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> ne</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">w report issued by the National Research Council</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The Effects of Solar Variability on Earth’s Climate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lays out some of the surprisingly complex ways that solar activity can make itself felt on our planet.”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  Also </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Jasper K</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">irby, Head of the CLOUD Experiment at CERN, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">recently gave </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">a presentation </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">showing strong correlations between cosmic rays, so</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lar cycles and earth’s climate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">He</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">nney </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">pointed out that the very costly green/decarbonizing agenda is neither particularly </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">effective in achieving its basic objectives or reducing CO2 emissions</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">because</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he few nuclear plants will </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">at a vast cost </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">have a marginal effect</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">CCS is not proven; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">wind farms </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">are not only expenisve, they </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">do not achieve what they claim on the tin</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> by way of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">mitigation of CO2; r</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">esidential solar makes offshore wind look cheap</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; and fresh cut wood chips masquerading as biomass actually increase CO2 emissions</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Nor will ou</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">r</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> effort do much if anything to save the planet</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">While the British government is obsessed with driving unabated coal plants off the system, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in 2012 the World Resources Institute identified 1,199 new coal fired plants with a capacity of 1400GW being proposed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  T</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">en 900MW new coal plants are being completed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in Germany and the Netherlands.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The IPCC failed to provide a sound assessment of the state of climate science.  We need a truly independent as</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">essm</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">e</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">nt undertaken by people who have no vested commercial or reputational interest in the outcome.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">David Hol</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">land </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">describes some of the abuses of process and of science in the first four ARs of the IPCC, summarizing “…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the IPCC process has</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">always been over presumptive of the scientific knowledge and has failed to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ensure that the experts, who serve it, meet the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">required professional and ethical</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">standards. The IPCC has conspicuously failed to ensure any compliance with its</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">fundamental principle of requiring a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“comprehensive, objective, open and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">transparent” </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">process.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Given, the views already formed by the majority</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of its founders and their</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lack of any enforcement of its Principles and Procedures, the IPCC is seen by</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">many as established to provide a justification for political commitment. For these</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span 