h we "feel some degree of discomfort"</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">we "need to use public</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> transport</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> much more</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">"</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">air travel should be taxed heavily enough to discourage u</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s from</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">flying</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">hotels should bill u</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s separately for our energy use”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">She concludes “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a child</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of one of the most politically riven bodies known to humanity, the United Nations</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">At a 2008 event celebrating the IPCC's 20th anniversary,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">chairman Pachauri told a group of IPCC insiders: "The UNFCCC is our main customer</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…A</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">n international treaty is a political instrument. This makes it impossible for any reasonable</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">person to conclude that the IPCC is about science for science sake.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">This is sci</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ence for politics’ </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sake.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Paul Matthews </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">an applied mathematician with expertise in fluid dynamics, mathematical modelling and</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">computer simulation. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He has </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">not worked directly in the field of climate science but h</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">as followed </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the field with interest for t</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he last 5 years.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  He </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">notes misleading claims about the likelihood of human influence that have little detailed justification.  He also notes cherry picking and misleading presentation of data.  He summarises “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">unfortunately the IPCC report is marred by a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">mi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sleading presentation, with some distortion of the facts and spin, particularly in the Summary for</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Policymakers. This is unscientific and casts doubt on the validity of the exercise and the credibility</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of the IPCC.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">John McLean’s </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">doctorate in Australia is</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> on climate issue</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  He wrote a book </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“We have been conned – an independent review of the IPCC” </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a detailed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">analysis of the flaws in previous IPCC reports. H</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e points out that in order to understand part of the agenda of the IPCC it is necessary to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">appreciate the history of its formation and that it “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is focussed on the narrow issue of any human influences on climate and has no mandate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">to examine all possible causes (which means it cites only material relevant to its</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">charter)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; it </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">benefits through the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">massive government funding to research aligned with the IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">view because such research produces a large number of peer-reviewed papers</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">attracts researchers who benefitted </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">from the research funding above</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> as Lead Authors</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and Coordinating Lead Authors</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">does</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> not include sceptical authors (and yet scepticism is an essential part of science)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is not independent of government and politics because government representatives</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">effectively dictate what will be said in the Summary for Policymakers</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> is ineffective because of its narrow focus and this distorts its outlook into a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">form of political justification</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He points out “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The writing of an IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Assessment Review i</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s made much easier if there is general</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">agreement between the Lead Authors and Coord</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">inating Lead Authors of a given chapter.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">One way to achieve this is to avoid involving any potential authors who might be sceptical of</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the claim of a significant human influence on temperature.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conor McMenamie </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is an inventor.  He opines that AR5 has an agenda to promote global climate </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">hange, and to support this by claiming the science is settled and rejecting other views.  He comments “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The climate research institutions, upon whom we rely for an honest and accur</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ate</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">provision of information, are quickly becoming the least reliable authorities at</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">providing that same information, since it is their ambition to adhere to the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">aspirations of the IPCC, despite their 100% failure record.”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Christopher Monkton, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">a well know</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">n </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, responded to the question of “How robust are the conclusions in AR5?” with an effective set of exhibits showing the discrepancy between various model predictions and aspects of global temperatures.  He linked the exhibits to 1) the failure of re</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">liability of the models; 2) the failure to explain the temperature hiatus; and 3) the lack of credibility of the IPCC.  In response to the question of whether AR5 reflected the range of scientific views he pointed out that he had not been allowed to attend</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> the initial scoping meeting for AR5 and the IPCC also tried to exclude Professor Paul Reiter, a world expert on epidemiology of malaria, who had disagreed with the IPCC line on the spread of malaria due to ACC.  He claimed “only one viewpoint is allowed”.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Monkton considered “There is no economic case for climate action…it is time to do away with the IPCC…There is no need to cut CO2 emissions…the climate scare is over.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Susan Morrow </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a retired science teacher and an amateur meteorologist/climatologist</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  She comments “The IPCC is 100% AGW lobbyists/scientists; there are</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">other climate groups/ scientists that are 100% the opposite</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  If</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Met O</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ffice wants to lead world climate research </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">it should not shun and demoralize alternative r</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">esearch</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, but employ </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">some </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AGW </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s on an equal basis.”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Philip Richen </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">has a PhD in theoretical physics.  He concludes </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">does not provide a balanced assessment of the scientific literature on natural</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">variability</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The report only partially addresses the r</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">eliability of climate models</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">…T</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">he report does not sufficiently explain the reasons for the hiatus in global temperature.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Fenton Robb </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">comments “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">IPCC AR5 is unashamedly presented, not as the outcome of scientific</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">observation, but as a compilation of the opi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">nions of a close community of experts.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">This is made abundantly clear in Sect</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ion A Introduction paragraph 3.”  He considers that “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Climatologists form a closely-knit peer group that shares an interest in promoting</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">public alarm and provoking continued </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">research.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Scottish Climate and Energy Forum </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">states that notwithstanding its claim to the contrary the IPCC does not know enough about climate science to model it accurately; it cannot determine the effects of climate change; and it provides no basi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s for government action.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Ian Strangeways </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">was head of Applied Physics at the Institute of Hydrology and is now Director of TerraData Ltd, a consultancy in environmental monitoring and measurement.  He </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">comments:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Models are still in the developmental, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">academic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> stage and are not proven tools</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The cause of the ‘pause’ in rising temperatures over</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> the last 15 years is not known</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Mixing politics with science is not cond</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ucive to scientific objectivity”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He developed the latter point that [IPCC] “B</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">eing a ‘Governmental’ organisation makes it difficult to summarise and report</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">scientific research objectively because of political pressures, interference,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">interpretation and spin. This is particularly so in the case of the Summary for</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Policymakers, which </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is all that most people read. The IPCC should, therefore, be</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">replaced by a purely scientific panel free from any political involvement whatsoever.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC is increasingly perceived by many as having a political agenda,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">undermining the excellent scientific</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> work behind it.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Richard Tol </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">is a professor of economics at the University of Sussex and of the economi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">cs of climate change at the Vrij</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e Universiteet Amsterdam.  He does not regard the IPCC as an effective mechanism for assessing scientific knowledge, co</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">mmenting “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC reports justify the existence of a large bureaucracy which, judging from the lack</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">in progress in reducing greenhouse gas emissions and vulnerability to climate change, seems</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">primarily occupied with maintaining and expanding said </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">bureaucracy.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">He also opines:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The UK could be a leader in international climate policy if it would demonstrate that</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">greenhouse gas emissions can be cut substantially without causing economic pain. Current</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">UK climate policy shows the opposite: Climate </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">policy can cause real hardship without</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">making a dent in emissions.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ASSESSMENT OF ASSESSMENT</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The British Warmist establishment took no notice of 1) the IPCC’s past promotion of pseudo science such as the “hockey stick” and “Himalayagate”; 2) its pas</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">t baseless claims of increased hurricanes and the spread of malaria due to ACC; 3) the exposure in Climategate of the unethical practices of a coterie of climate scientists involved with the IPCC; 4) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">its </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">association with the inconvenient inaccuracies promo</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ted by Senator Al Gore; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and 5) the various shortcomings cited in the previous two sections</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  It continued living in its politically correct bubble of consensus settled science, claiming</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The conclusions of the AR5 Physical Science Basis Report are robust and there is little to question – </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">there is significant dissent from this proposition</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Much, if not most, of the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">science is settled – </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">not true</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 reflects the views of most scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> - </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">w</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">hile this </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">is true of British state scientists, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">it is not true </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">of a number of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">f</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ree thinker</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">s in foreign countries</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">All avoided discussion of, or attempted to finesse the unreliability of models  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Yet the July draft of the report stated clearly </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“Models do not</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> generally reproduce the observed reduction in surface warming trend over the last 10-15 years” (Section D-1, Draft SPM-10).  This statement was removed from the final, published version of the SPM</span><a name="_ftnref18"></a><a href="#_ftn18">[18]</a></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">All danced around the issue of whether AR5 has sufficien</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">tly explained the hiatus in the global surface temperature - </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">i.e. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">like the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">they cannot explain it</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">and are </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">reduced to speculation that the heat was hiding in the deep ocean without explaining how it got there without the upper ocean warming</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 confir</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ms the need for urgent global action to address climate change - </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">there is significant dissent from this proposition</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC is an effective mechanism for assessing scientific knowledge and it has not been politicized.  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Several </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> and public policy </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ubmissions </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">give cogent</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> and fact based </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">reasons for disagreeing</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">AR5 supports the government’s effort to cut CO2 emissions – </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">many disagree</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">I</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">n view of the close involvement of the various organisations</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> and people in the IPCC none can be regarded as independent judges of AR5.  Furthermore they variously have political face, grant income</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">, expenditure on bigger and faster computers</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">and reputations at stake.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> main scientific</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> criticisms of AR5 are:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There is no substantive evidence to support the IPCC’s claimed linkage between the warming of the climate and increasing CO2</span><a name="_ftnref19"></a><a href="#_ftn19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> – the conclusions of the IPCC are not robust; there is scope to question many asp</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">cts of the science</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">onvey</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> “an alarmist evaluation of the influence on the climate of anthropogenic CO2 emissions that does not properly reflect scientific knowledge”, with distortions for political purposes</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The models </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">do not reflect reality</span><a name="_ftnref20"></a><a href="#_ftn20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> can be fudged with high </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">climate </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sensi</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">tivity; and “are not getting any better”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  T</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">hey are of little or no value in explaining the past, let alone</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> predicting </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the future</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The handling of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">uncertainties (e.g. claiming something is 95% certain) is shocking and deeply unscientific</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There was a fai</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">lure to assess climate sensitivity from observational estimates which are suggesting much lower figures than used in the IPCC models</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">re was a failure to examine natural variability; the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">role of clouds and water vapour</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> are not properly understood; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the contribution of methane has not been properly analysed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the possible </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">effect of the sun </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">was effectively dismissed</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  The science is definitely not settled</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The issue of the 15 or so year pause in global temperature has not been properly addressed…”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">re are factual errors in the science</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Public policy criticisms are that the IPCC process is not all that it is cracked up to be, notably:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It is not exclusively the work of independent scientists.  The chairman; the head of WG1, and some of the lead </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">authors have strong green activist credentials</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.  “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC authors, who have the last word on the material to be included, were selected because they were known to agree with the "consensus" and thus the final product is simply the consensus of those who </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">agree with the consensus.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> Were there any "</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sceptic</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">al" Lead Authors to provide the true ra</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">nge of views on climate change? No”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“The growing implications of the complexity of the climate change problem and its potential solutions are becoming increasingly ap</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">parent, highlighting the inadequacies of the ‘consensus to power’ approach for decision making on the complex issues associated with climate change” - </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">there are many unknowns in climate science</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Apart from</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Britain</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> where climate science is dominated by pol</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">itically correct state scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">there is no sound basis for claims of an </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">overwhelming </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">international consensus</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">It uses evasive and obfuscatory wording to cover over issues which are embarrassing.  Thus it had this to say </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:Georgia; font-size:12pt">about climate model </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:Georgia; font-size:12pt">performance:-</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“Climate models have improved since the [</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal">Fourth Assessment Report</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">published in 2007]. Models reproduce observed continental-scale surface temperature patterns and trends over many decades, including the more rapid warming since the mid-20th c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">entury and the cooling immediately following large volcanic eruptions (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal">very</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal">high confidence</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">).”</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">     Followed immediately by</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">this</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">:-</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“The long-term climate model simulations show a trend in global-mean surface temperature from 1951 to 2012 that agrees with</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> the observed trend (</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal">very high confidence</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">). There are, however, differences between simulated and observed trends over periods as short as 10 to 15 years (e.g., 1998 to 2012).”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There is general agreement among the commentators that the SPM is a p</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">olitically contrived document. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The IPCC has failed to ensure any compliance with its fundamental principle of requiring a </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“comprehensive, objective, open and transparent” </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">process</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Several</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> propose that the IPCC is past its sell by date, and some </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">argue there</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> is a need for a genuinely independent assessment of the realities of climate science</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“AR</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">5 conclusions fatally weaken the economic case for policy action. Both the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">level of, and confidence in, temperature </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">projections are sharply reduced”</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The proposal to </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">rely on renewables is impracticable given 1) their high costs and 2) their profligate use of land.  They will not meet the future needs of a highly urbanized world of 9bn people</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The British attempts at decarbonisation are both ineffectual, expensive, illu</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">sory tokenism that will not nothing to save the planet</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><a href="http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/ipcc-principles/ipcc-principles.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/ipcc-principles/ipcc-principles.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">This is the total on 20/12 plus those of Professors Judith Curry and John Christy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Viz those by Brigitte Nerlich and by James Painter focused more on communication than the science and poli</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">cy implications of AR5.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Viz those by Carbon Tracker and EDF Energy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">i.e. those who claim that climate warming over the period 1996-1998 is mainly – if not entirely – a consequence of CO2 emissions due to mankind.  Note that in the period prior to 1976 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">there was concern about global cooling while since 1998 the surface temperature has been stable</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">the so called “hiatus” or “pause”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.  That does not stop the more enthusiastic warmists claiming that the earth is still warming, perhaps with the heat going int</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">o the deep ocean</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> where it cannot be measured!</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Donna Laframboise points out the green credentials of some of the lead authors, see</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> 3</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">The key people are the 209 Lead Authors who control the input</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">which is accepted from Review Editors and Contributing </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Authors and control the drafting.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">This is a stretch;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> m</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">ost – if not all – of those involved are employees of governmental organizations or universities.  They are not putting in </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">their </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">time and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">their </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">money.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Interestingly this included the Imperial Granth</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">am.  However, in an interview with the Economist on 18/3/10 Professor Hoskins stated of climate models “they’re still pretty lousy.”  Clearly the submission is being politically correct.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Sceptics</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> are those who accept that the climate is (as ever) changing and warmed up from 1976 to 1998, but that the reasons for the warming are complex and far from fully understood, and cannot all be laid at the door of CO2 emissions due to mankind.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">He notes tha</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">t </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">the IPCC relies on climate models to distinguish “natural” from “human” caused climate change</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">, but “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">these </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">m</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">odels on average fail by a significant amount to reproduce the climate of the past 35 years</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">…the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> IPCC now has even more confidence that the models c</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">an distinguish “natural” from “human” change over a period the models clearly fail to simulate well. It doesn’t make sense to me.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> In an interview for EconTalk with Russ Roberts of Stanford </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">University </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">he commented how unusual her approach was in the feb</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">rile environment of climate science.  Her interview</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> is on her blog judithcurry.com, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">JC interview with EconTalk, 23 December 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn13"></a><a href="#_ftnref13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Curry, Judith, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">2013</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> IPCC diagnosis – permanent paradigm paralysis. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">Climate Etc. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">(blog)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a href="http://judithcurry.com/2013/09/28/ipcc-diagnosis-permanent-paradigm-paralysis/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://judithcurry.com/2013/09/28/ipcc-diagnosis-permanent-paradigm-paralysis/</span></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn14"></a><a href="#_ftnref14">[14]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">The paper shows the failure of 97.5% of 90 climate models to track temperatur</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">e over the period 1983 to 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn15"></a><a href="#_ftnref15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">CO2 without amplification or positive feedbacks cannot warm the atmosphere in the mann</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">er proposed by IPCC scientists and a doubling world other things being equal increase the global temperature by about 1</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C. The IPCC and climate models assume positive feedback which amplifies the effect.  Thus the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">IPCC AR4 conclusion on climate sensitivity is as:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">“The equilibrium climate sensitivity…is likely to be in the range 2</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C to 4.5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C with a best estimate of about 3</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C and is very unlikely to be less than 1.5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C.  Values higher than 4.5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C cannot be excluded…”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">It is the increase in sensitivity which leads to the predictions of significant future increases in temperature.  AR5 avoided setting an official </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">figure</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> for climate sensitivity beca</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">use of disagreement</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">re are two measures of sensitivity.  The first is Equilibrium Climate Sensitivity (ECS), which is the equilibrium change in global mean near surface air temperature that would result from a sustaine</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">d doubling of CO2 concentration.  The second is Transient Climate Response (TCR), which is the average temperature respo0nse over a 20 year period.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn16"></a><a href="#_ftnref16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">The World Climate Research Programme established the Coupled Model Intercomparison</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> Project (CMIP) to study the output of coupled atmosphere – ocean ge</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">neral circulation models.  CMIP3</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> we</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">re the models developed for AR4 and CIMP5 for AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn17"></a><a href="#_ftnref17">[17]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> “The Delinquent Teenager: IPCC exposé”</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">“Into the Dustbin</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">: Rajendra Pachauri, the Climate Report </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">and the Nobel Peace Prize</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">” (which is available as a pdf from her website, nofrakkingconcensus.com)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn18"></a><a href="#_ftnref18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Accor</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">ding to Monckton at the request of representatives </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">of the German and Hungarian</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> governments</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn19"></a><a href="#_ftnref19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">I have read a number of papers by the Met Office and o</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">thers purporting to claim ACC.  A noted characteristic of most of them is a reliance on models to show whatever (e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">a “probabilistic” seeming </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">distribution to outcomes) followed by an assertion that the event is probably due to ACC</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">, but in reality there i</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">s no empirical link</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.  I call this “</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">int</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">ellectual fluff”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">In “Solar and planetary oscillation control on climate change: hind-cast, forecast and a comparison with the CMIP5 GCMs”, Nicola Scafetta of Duke University argues that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">“global surface temperature </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">records since 1850 are characterized by climatic oscillations synchronous with specific solar, planetary and lunar harmonics superimposed on a background warming modulation. The latter is related to a long millennial solar oscillation and to changes in the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> chemical composition of the atmosphere (e.g. aerosol and greenhouse gases). However, current general circulation climate models, e.g. the CMIP5 GCMs, to be used in the AR5 IPCC Report in 2013, fail to reconstruct the observed climatic oscillations. As an </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">alternate, an empirical model is proposed that uses</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">a specific set of decadal, multidecadal, secular and millennial astronomic harmonics to simulate the observed climatic oscillations…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">and performs the GCMs by better hindcasting the observed 1850-2012 clima</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">te patterns…</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">about 50-60% of the warming observed since 1850 and since 1970 was induced by natural oscillations likely resulting from harmonic astronomical forcings that are not yet included in the GCMs.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p></body></html>